<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="208" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,647,514,603]" pageId="3" pageNumber="208">DISTRIBUTION. — Northeastern forest, from the Bay of Antongil to the Montagnes des Français.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,646,637,756]" pageId="3" pageNumber="208">
Distinguished by its short stipules (&lt;
<quantity box="[562,634,637,664]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="208" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
), large leaves (up to 17 
<emphasis box="[346,361,668,693]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="208">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[368,423,668,694]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="208" unit="cm" value="7.0">7 cm</quantity>
) with entire margins (juvenile leaves may be dentate, however), 3 sepals, 12-16 stamens, 4-6 carpels and unlobed fruit.
</paragraph>
